result.execSummary:
The defendant Consuelo Gonzalez Morales was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Resisting or Obstructing an Officer, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.41(1).
  • Disorderly Conduct, a class B misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 947.01(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Case Called @ 3:52 PM: Defendant Consuelo Gonzalez Morales in court, appearing in person, pro se.  Steven Paul Anderson appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Enrique Soria present as Interpreter.   Interpreter oath given by the Court.  Court notes for the record how long this case has been pending  and the forfeiture of the cash bond.  Court questions Defendant as to her lack of contact with the Court.  Defendant states she had Immigration concerns and could not contact the  Court.   She has no funds available for counsel retainer.  Court will make a Dean Appt (Chelsie Thuecks).  Argument as to bond by ADA - 2 nonappearances with 2 cash bonds now forfeited.  Argues for $1000 to $1500 w/conditions.  Defendant makes statement as to bond request - states she can make payments on the bond.  The Court:  Will appoint counsel.  No later than 2/3/2017 she must post $250 deposit for Ct Appt Atty Fees with 3/1/2017 a $100 per mo PP.  Bond ordered of $1500 cash - due to 2 missed Court appearances and lack of contact.  STC Scheduled with Counsel.  Status conference scheduled for February 20, 2017 at 03:30 pm.
